thread.title: Prep Volleyball: Blair Oaks sweeps Rock Bridge
thread.title_full: Prep Volleyball: Blair Oaks sweeps Rock Bridge

author: News Tribune
title: Prep Volleyball: Blair Oaks sweeps Rock Bridge
text:
COLUMBIA, Mo. —The Blair Oaks Lady Falcons defeated the Rock Bridge Bruins on three levels Thursday. 
Blair Oaks won the varsity match 25-15, 25-18. 
Sadie Turner dished out 11 assists, while Jayde Peters had eight, Ryan Dudenhoeffer had eight blocks, while Rebecca Schroeder finished with six. Paige Rackers had six kills and Taylor Stockman totaled four. Alexa Stegemann finished with four aces for the Lady Falcons (23-2-1). 
In the JV match, Blair Oaks was a 25-16, 25-21 winner. 
Lanie Lowry had 10 kills. Ali Juergensmeyer had 14 assists, while Emily Yaeger totaled 10. Claire Heckman had 11 digs and Vicky Turner added seven for the Lady Falcons (20-0). 
In the C match, Blair Oaks won 22-25, 25-22, 15-12. 
Katelyn Weber had 17 digs, while Claire Smith and Madalyn Temmen had six assists each. Sydney Rackers had seven kills, while Sydney Nivens had two blocks for the Lady Falcons (11-4-1). 
Blair Oaks will play Saturday at the Versailles Tournament. ﻿
